class src.environment.ros_social_gym.RosSocialEnv(*args, launch_config: str = '/home/rosdev/social_gym/config/gym_gen/launch.launch', observer: Observer = None, rewarder: Rewarder = None, scenarios: List[Scenario] = (), num_humans: int | Tuple[int, int] = (5, 25), num_agents: int | Tuple[int, int] = (3, 5), debug: bool = False, visuals=None, **kwargs)

Bases: ParallelEnv, EzPickle

A ros-based social navigation environment for OpenAI gym supporting MultiAgent training.

A lot of the documentation is taken from https://pettingzoo.farama.org/content/environment_creation/ which is almost entirely about supporting multiple agents in the environment.
